12/06/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- War crimes suspect Veselin Sljivancanin, wanted by the UN tribunal for alleged involvement in the 1991 Vukovar massacre, is no longer in Serbia-Montenegro, Belgrade-based Radio B92 reported Wednesday (11 June), quoting a lobbying group. The secretary of a committee supporting Sljivancanin said it had advised him to leave the country if he wanted to survive. The group insists that he be tried at home. (Radio B92 - 11/06/03)
